article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 59, St. Peter's 58
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Gerald Robinson scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Tennessee-Martin edged St. Peter's 59-58 Saturday night in a late non-conference game. Tennessee-Martin (8-22) led 30-25 at halftime and dominated on the boards, outrebounding St. Peter's (4-23) 48-37. Akeem Gooding scored 15 points for St. Peter's (4-23), which had a 58-52 lead with 2:30 to play. Robinson hit two free throws with 24 seconds left to give Tennessee-Martin the final lead. Cleve Woodfork added 14 points and 10 rebounds for Tennessee-Martin. Todd Sowell scored 10 and Raul Orta had 13 for St. Peter's.
